				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I know someone already posted this but I just wanted to confirm that neg CHA does NOT make fear spells and charm spells last longer for necroes. I don't know where people got that idea in the first place. People ask me &quot;then why do so many necro items have -CHA?&quot; Umm... RP purposes? Necroes aren't supposed to be exactly charismatic, so items that make them more powerful will make them even less so. There's a mask that drops in LoIO, it's -25 CHA, everytime drop off a common as dirt lvl 20 mob. Now if -CHA for necroes was so great, why would Verant put such a friggin uber item on such a low lvl mob?<BR>
<BR>
In fact, POSITIVE CHA helps a necro's charm spells and Screaming Terror work better. I don't think it has an effect on Fear either way. That being said, I bought this robe for my necro today (for 1.5k and a 1k item) and am very happy with it... it looks great and as long as it doesn't give -15 INT I don't care about the stats.
